============================================================
Plan I patch for PETSc 3.25.1 + oneAPI 2025.3.3 + KokkosKernels
+ Hypre master + Intel Arc Pro B70 (Battlemage)
============================================================
Date:    2026-05-08
Stack:   ESI OpenFOAM v2512 / PETSc 3.25.1 / oneAPI 2025.3.3
         (= 2025.3.2.21 filename, build 2025.3.3.20260319)
         / KokkosKernels 5.1.0 (BATCHED=OFF) / Hypre master
         / Kokkos / Umpire / Caliper

Problem: KokkosKernels 5.1.0's BatchedDblBufGemm has a non-trivially-
copyable reference member, violating SYCL kernel-parameter strict-
spec enforced by icpx 2025.3+. Affects KokkosKernels' own ETI builds
for SYCL+SYCLSPACE+double. Cannot be disabled via CMake flag because
SPARSE/GRAPH/ALL_COMPONENTS each FORCE-enable BATCHED in
kokkoskernels_components.cmake.

Strategy:
  (1) Pre-build a patched KokkosKernels-5.1.0 tarball where SPARSE/
      GRAPH/ALL no longer FORCE BATCHED ON. Pass to PETSc as
      --download-kokkos-kernels=file:///path/to/patched.tar.gz so
      PETSc uses our local source instead of git-cloning fresh.
  (2) Patch the single PETSc file (aijkok.kokkos.cxx) that calls
      KokkosBatched directly: replace MatInvertVariableBlockDiagonal_
      SeqAIJKokkos body with a SETERRQ stub.
  (3) Use Hypre develop/master via --download-hypre-commit=origin/master
      to avoid DPL/DPCT 2025.3 internal mismatch in release Hypre.
  (4) Use oneAPI 2025.3.3 (NOT 2026.0): aligns with PMZFX-validated
      stack for B70 and avoids the icpx-2026 vs DPCT-2025.3 mismatch.
      (Intel deprecated DPCT for 2026; 2025.3 is the last consistent
      stack.)
  (5) Runtime: pass -use_gpu_aware_mpi 0 since System-OpenMPI is not
      SYCL-GPU-aware. Use Hypre BoomerAMG smoother name "l1scaled-
      jacobi" (master); release name was "l1-Jacobi".

Loss:
  - VPB-Jacobi (Variable Point-Block Jacobi) PC for MATSEQAIJKOKKOS
    no longer functional (runtime SETERRQ if requested).
  - PETSc's ex3k tutorial fails on aijkokkos+ILU0 due to IGC
    (Intel Graphics Compiler) Internal Compiler Error during SYCL
    JIT of KokkosSparse spiluk on Battlemage. Independent of our
    patches; backend bug. Tolerated; ex19 and ex19+HYPRE pass.

============================================================
Patch 1 — kokkos-kernels-5.1.0/cmake/kokkoskernels_components.cmake
============================================================
Comment-out three FORCE-enable lines for BATCHED in the
SPARSE, GRAPH, and ALL_COMPONENTS conditional blocks:

@@ Three sites @@
-  set(KokkosKernels_ENABLE_COMPONENT_BATCHED ON CACHE BOOL "" FORCE)
+  # Plan I disabled (was:   set(KokkosKernels_ENABLE_COMPONENT_BATCHED ON CACHE BOOL "" FORCE))

Reproduction:
  cd /opt/openfoam-v2512/tarballs
  wget https://github.com/kokkos/kokkos-kernels/archive/refs/tags/5.1.0.tar.gz
  tar xzf 5.1.0.tar.gz
  sed -i 's|^  set(KokkosKernels_ENABLE_COMPONENT_BATCHED ON CACHE BOOL "" FORCE)$|  # Plan I disabled (was: \0)|' \
    kokkos-kernels-5.1.0/cmake/kokkoskernels_components.cmake
  tar czf kokkos-kernels-5.1.0-plan-i.tar.gz kokkos-kernels-5.1.0

